{
  "text": "The Box and Blocks test is an assessment of manual dexterity. Participants transferred blocks over a partition one at a time as fast as possible, and the number of blocks transferred in 60 s were counted [CITATION_1] . Box and Blocks Z-scores were calculated using normative data for the left or non-dominant hand from Mathiowetz et al. [CITATION_2] for ages 6-19 years and Jongbloed-Pereboom et al. [CITATION_3] for ages 3-5 years.",
